And the last is really the sharing expertise, because as you, the audience, there are lots

00:18:35.160 --> 00:18:38.599
of experts that are there.

00:18:38.599 --> 00:18:41.800
And then we can work together on even better solutions.

00:18:41.800 --> 00:18:48.359
But one thing I want to bring more from the personalized medicine, does one size fits

00:18:48.359 --> 00:18:55.160
all, meaning are we, as a pharma, doing the same efforts but differently?

00:18:56.040 --> 00:18:59.880
So what is the impact on our collaboration in this space?

00:18:59.880 --> 00:19:08.119
Because if we now look at an example of those open source packages that are under the pharma

00:19:08.119 --> 00:19:13.000
verse, we can try to build on this together.

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:19.880
And I'm here today also to bring you two successful examples on the collaboration.

00:19:19.880 --> 00:19:29.800
One, thank you for our internal team who implemented TrueFont and RTF for the R tables,

00:19:29.800 --> 00:19:33.079
something that I will showcase in a minute.

00:19:33.079 --> 00:19:40.280
But also the other solution that probably our internal team also brought and brought

00:19:40.280 --> 00:19:48.359
in an idea and was commonly implemented, something that was less than two weeks ago,

00:19:48.920 --> 00:19:53.479
was release a so-called transform module output.

00:19:53.479 --> 00:19:55.959
So let me go through those two examples.

00:19:56.520 --> 00:20:02.920
First of all, for the static output, as I said, implementation of the TrueFont might

00:20:02.920 --> 00:20:08.599
have a big impact on your organization and the way you implement.

00:20:08.599 --> 00:20:15.000
Because on the left-hand side, this is an example of the demographic table from this

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:16.839
source, from the TLG catalog.

00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:24.760
And with our work and our internal efforts, we made it to actually have the same number,

00:20:24.760 --> 00:20:26.119
but looking differently.

00:20:26.119 --> 00:20:34.280
Regardless what will be the format, whether it will be RTF or the X format or something,

00:20:35.319 --> 00:20:40.680
some companies might have different needs for the feel and look of those outputs.

00:20:40.680 --> 00:20:47.239
So this is an example how our work contributed to the community.

00:20:47.800 --> 00:20:51.479
But more exciting is actually the interactive part.

00:20:52.040 --> 00:20:59.640
Here you can see the screenshot from maybe you've already seen this before, the TL module

00:20:59.640 --> 00:21:03.239
association between two variables, race and biomarker.

