You can think about adding the show R code that will create this true font output in

00:22:48.599 --> 00:22:49.160
the future.

00:22:49.800 --> 00:22:56.520
And with this one, I'd like to thank you and we'll invite now Mark, who will go through

00:22:56.520 --> 00:22:57.880
the lessons learned.

00:22:58.359 --> 00:23:03.560
Yeah, like Nick already explained that our exciting journey has been more than just coding.

00:23:04.199 --> 00:23:07.719
It has been a voyage filled with learning and growth.

00:23:08.520 --> 00:23:15.239
And as I unwrap our lessons learned, I remember the wise words, I would say experience is

00:23:15.239 --> 00:23:17.800
the teacher of all things.

00:23:17.800 --> 00:23:20.359
So, now let's look at six key takeaways.

00:23:20.359 --> 00:23:24.040
And the first you're already seeing is training and knowledge development.

00:23:24.680 --> 00:23:30.119
So, foundational knowledge is crucial and investing in a comprehensive training tailored

00:23:30.119 --> 00:23:36.359
to a diverse audience ensures everyone from statisticians to statistical programmers has

00:23:36.359 --> 00:23:38.359
a solid grasp of R.

00:23:39.400 --> 00:23:46.520
Try also diverse learning resources by utilizing a mix of online courses, workshops, and dynamic

00:23:46.520 --> 00:23:47.800
coding sessions.

00:23:47.800 --> 00:23:54.199
You really can cater to various learning styles and boosting engagement and understanding.

00:23:54.760 --> 00:24:00.199
I also really like to do a shout out to our statistics colleagues here for really helping

00:24:00.199 --> 00:24:02.760
us tailor some of those trainings.

00:24:03.640 --> 00:24:06.040
Now, onto infrastructure and scalability.

00:24:06.040 --> 00:24:10.280
Understanding that a strong infrastructure is essential for moving to R.

00:24:11.239 --> 00:24:13.560
Packages are upgraded or added.

00:24:13.560 --> 00:24:16.359
Also, interactive use cases, they really grow.

00:24:16.760 --> 00:24:21.000
We really must ensure that our infrastructure can keep pace.

00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:27.239
A big shout out to IT, especially Satish Murthy's team here for their fantastic support

00:24:27.239 --> 00:24:30.520
and helping us making the right infrastructure choices.

00:24:31.400 --> 00:24:31.900
Next.

00:24:33.880 --> 00:24:40.040
So, when it comes to standardization, remember that consistent practices really help create

00:24:40.040 --> 00:24:46.040
smoother collaboration using the same framework and packages as well as standardized R code

00:24:46.040 --> 00:24:52.280
repositories improve not only code quality but also help collaboration across teams.

00:24:52.280 --> 00:24:56.599
And we're using basically they are the same building blocks, the same tools.

00:24:56.599 --> 00:25:01.000
So, that really helps all the teams in using R and Shiny.

00:25:01.959 --> 00:25:02.459
Next.

00:25:03.560 --> 00:25:09.640
And I think this one is one of the most important lessons is the power, of course, of the open

00:25:09.640 --> 00:25:10.599
source community.

00:25:10.599 --> 00:25:13.800
That's also where you guys are really coming into play.

00:25:13.800 --> 00:25:19.719
The vibrant R community offers a treasure trove of packages, resources, and support,

00:25:19.719 --> 00:25:23.959
which really accelerate learning and foster innovation.

00:25:25.560 --> 00:25:27.640
Now, what about change management?

00:25:27.640 --> 00:25:32.839
Well, identifying early adopters is key for broader acceptance of R.

00:25:33.400 --> 00:25:39.319
For example, when they showcase its interactive potential, like Todd already did, it really

00:25:39.319 --> 00:25:45.479
sparks the interest and it really encourages participation of all the members in our

00:25:45.479 --> 00:25:46.280
organization.

00:25:47.000 --> 00:25:49.079
Phased implementation works best.

00:25:49.079 --> 00:25:55.400
So, gradual rollouts for different compounds or studies allows smoother transition.

00:25:56.119 --> 00:26:02.760
The opportunity for iterative improvements is also there as well because you do it more

00:26:02.760 --> 00:26:03.400
gradually.

00:26:03.479 --> 00:26:07.160
And finally, risk mitigation and scaling strategies.

00:26:07.160 --> 00:26:10.760
Well, pilot programs are invaluable.

00:26:10.760 --> 00:26:18.280
And these pilot programs in using R helps us identifying challenges early on, providing

00:26:18.280 --> 00:26:24.280
crucial lessons for us as we scale up and integrating R into our daily routines.

00:26:24.280 --> 00:26:31.079
That one is also essential for a smooth transition to what we call business as usual with continued

00:26:31.079 --> 00:26:31.719
support.

00:26:31.880 --> 00:26:34.280
With continued support and resources.

00:26:35.000 --> 00:26:37.800
I think that wraps up the lessons learned effectively.

00:26:37.800 --> 00:26:40.680
So, now let's explore some best practices.

00:26:44.199 --> 00:26:49.880
So, first, an obvious but really important one, it's already mentioned a couple of times,

00:26:49.880 --> 00:26:53.000
is the area of training and knowledge development.

00:26:53.000 --> 00:26:58.599
So, it's really important to establish a structured training program tailored to different

00:26:58.599 --> 00:27:00.920
audiences and various learning styles.

00:27:01.800 --> 00:27:07.079
This program should be designed to be updated as new tools and techniques emerge within

00:27:07.079 --> 00:27:09.160
the R ecosystem.

00:27:09.160 --> 00:27:14.359
And we also need to train, of course, our team on the new standard ways of working with

00:27:14.359 --> 00:27:17.239
R and the packages to be used there as well.

00:27:18.199 --> 00:27:22.680
Next, let's move on to culture and engagement.

00:27:22.680 --> 00:27:29.479
It is crucial to foster a culture of curiosity and, of course, really embrace that open source

00:27:29.479 --> 00:27:30.520
mindset.

00:27:30.520 --> 00:27:36.280
We should encourage team members to explore both static and interactive R applications

00:27:36.280 --> 00:27:38.680
while promoting a hands-on learning approach.

00:27:39.319 --> 00:27:45.560
By adopting that open source mindset, we cannot only leverage the vast array of resources

00:27:45.560 --> 00:27:50.520
available in the community, but also we can contribute back to that community.

00:27:50.520 --> 00:27:53.800
Enhancing, again, collaboration and innovation.

00:27:54.760 --> 00:27:57.719
Now, let's talk about documentation and infrastructure.

00:27:57.719 --> 00:28:01.719
It's essential to document our infrastructure choices thoroughly.

00:28:02.359 --> 00:28:06.760
For instance, which validated packages can be found on which container?

00:28:07.959 --> 00:28:11.640
And additionally, building a knowledge sharing platform is also key.

00:28:11.640 --> 00:28:18.359
So, having sort of an R portal, for example, is an important, very important step of having

00:28:18.359 --> 00:28:24.359
one-stop shop of all information related to that R journey that you're doing and sharing

00:28:24.359 --> 00:28:26.920
that with your audience.

00:28:28.359 --> 00:28:34.040
In terms of feedback and continuous improvement, we need to create feedback loops because implementing

00:28:34.040 --> 00:28:39.719
feedback mechanism really helps us refine our processes and infrastructure based on

00:28:39.719 --> 00:28:41.959
what we learn and the needs of our teams.

00:28:42.680 --> 00:28:49.239
We should also monitor as well and assess how well R is being adopted to find and to

00:28:49.239 --> 00:28:51.719
enhance our approaches there.

00:28:51.719 --> 00:28:55.560
So, a little bit of metrics is also something that is very helpful.

00:28:56.439 --> 00:28:59.079
Now, moving on to demonstrations and adoption.

00:29:00.199 --> 00:29:05.319
We provide, yeah, providing compelling use cases that highlight the benefits of moving

00:29:05.319 --> 00:29:10.839
to R, showcasing both the static as well as the interactive projects is really important.

00:29:10.839 --> 00:29:17.000
Creating interactive demonstrations alongside the static examples can really serve to inspire

00:29:17.000 --> 00:29:24.520
the broader, yeah, the broader use among the teams in illustrating how both methods can

00:29:24.520 --> 00:29:29.959
complement each other effectively in various contexts, and also the shiny days like mentioned

00:29:29.959 --> 00:29:36.359
by Nick that can really, really help to showcase some of the adoption of R already.

00:29:36.920 --> 00:29:42.040
And lastly, regarding change management, we need to plan for the change and making sure

00:29:42.040 --> 00:29:44.839
that the business is ready to move to R.

00:29:44.839 --> 00:29:50.199
Also have a plan in place to deal with resistance is key, I would say, and addressing any concerns

00:29:50.199 --> 00:29:54.920
proactively can ensure, of course, smoother adoption of R.

00:29:56.520 --> 00:30:02.359
So, yeah, to wrap up this lessons learned and best practices session, I want to stress

00:30:02.359 --> 00:30:09.000
that success really comes from ongoing efforts and resilience, so every step that you take

00:30:09.000 --> 00:30:13.160
gets you closer to your goals, so embrace the challenges, I would say, because they

00:30:13.160 --> 00:30:15.640
are key building blocks on your road to success.

00:30:16.199 --> 00:30:22.439
Adopting R and an open-source mindset, yeah, is a journey that takes time, patience, and

00:30:22.439 --> 00:30:23.640
dedication.

00:30:23.640 --> 00:30:29.239
The initial learning curve might seem to be a little steep, but the value of your investment

00:30:29.239 --> 00:30:30.760
is really, really huge.

00:30:31.479 --> 00:30:36.199
So this approach not only encourages, I think, collaboration and progress for everyone who's

00:30:36.199 --> 00:30:42.199
involved, but also boosts, yeah, your individual skills as well and creating a shared environment

00:30:42.199 --> 00:30:48.760
where we build knowledge together, yeah, that is something that I can really, yeah,

00:30:48.760 --> 00:30:50.920
value and I'm really enthusiastic about.

00:30:52.040 --> 00:30:57.400
And with that, I would like to hand it over back to Nick to talk about some future opportunities.

