Yes, there are also some challenges with matching the SAS output.

00:38:43.399 --> 00:38:45.080
So yeah, of course, we tried.

00:38:45.719 --> 00:38:51.399
But we also had some R codes that, yeah, there were new outputs also created.

00:38:51.399 --> 00:38:54.040
But we tried to match, of course, as much as possible.

00:38:55.560 --> 00:38:58.760
There is also something to mention, I think, is there the GAMIS project.

00:38:58.760 --> 00:39:05.719
So really, you have some of the statistical results or the processes that you sometimes

00:39:05.719 --> 00:39:12.360
use, they are a little bit different in SAS, the procedures compared to the ones in R.

00:39:12.360 --> 00:39:15.000
And there's where GAMIS really comes and plays in.

00:39:15.000 --> 00:39:20.439
So I really advise you to go to the GAMIS to really see if there are differences between

00:39:20.439 --> 00:39:21.320
the different outputs.

00:39:21.320 --> 00:39:23.959
But we tried to match as much as possible.

00:39:27.080 --> 00:39:27.399
Thanks.

00:39:27.399 --> 00:39:27.719
Awesome.

00:39:30.120 --> 00:39:33.719
