00:46:29.719 --> 00:46:30.840
just walked through.

00:46:30.840 --> 00:46:32.760
And that container is there.

00:46:33.800 --> 00:46:34.840
We can spin it back up.

00:46:34.840 --> 00:46:37.959
We can reproduce outputs with it at any point in time.

00:46:37.959 --> 00:46:42.120
And then you can just think, OK, well, we released the container today.

00:46:42.120 --> 00:46:43.639
What new packages have been requested?

00:46:43.639 --> 00:46:45.399
Let's work towards the next container.

00:46:45.399 --> 00:46:47.560
And then we'll have another release later in the year.

