00:49:14.120 --> 00:49:17.639
So it is the use case that you need to bring in.

00:49:17.639 --> 00:49:24.760
And basically, Shiny has a lot of advantage if you're working on a statistical report

00:49:24.760 --> 00:49:26.520
and visualization.

00:49:26.520 --> 00:49:34.040
It has a strong stat part of analysis and creation with the R ecosystem.

00:49:35.320 --> 00:49:39.159
You don't need to go back and do a different language or something like that.

00:49:39.159 --> 00:49:44.439
So do your coding, back-end coding, and modularize it.

00:49:44.439 --> 00:49:48.679
And then kind of plug that modules into your Shiny framework.

00:49:48.679 --> 00:49:52.120
And publishing it would be a nice combination.

